<br>
Sebilis : possibly the greatest pickup dungeon of all time. 2 zone outs, 1 zone in. Zone in is 100% safe under normal circumstances. Mobs (at the time) hit hard enough to be difficult, but not so difficult that most players couldn't run from ZI to ZO if they had to. Reasonably easy to get to most camps. Rating 9.5 out of 10.<br>
<br>
Chardok : Zone in safe under normal circumstances. Zone in and Zone out in seperate locations, but the pathing, aggro and mob difficulty of the original Chardok made it too difficult. High numbers of shadowknight and indoor sow casting shamen. Extremely difficult to get anywhere much past the fort. Rating 6.6 out of 10.<br>
<br>
Charasis : Zone in completely unsafe. Requires either a rogue or farming for no drop keys to get anywhere past the zone in. Zone in and Zone out very far apart (so much so that it is not feasable to run, even if it were physically possible). High density of mobs (much too high considering the gear that was available at the time), many shadowknights. Negative faction hits for evil races. Rating 4.2 out of 10.<br>
<br>
Karnors : Zone out and zone in at same location. Many shaman mobs. Bad pathing. Many trains. What's worse is, due to bad pathing, any train is almost sure to hit every xp group between it and the zone line (unless you are in the basement). Negative faction hits for evil races. Rating 2.4 out of 10.<br>
<br>
It wasn't so much the fact that the zone in and zone out were in seperate places, but the difficulty of getting from zone in to zone out, or from camp to zone out. <p>Thedosius Dreamtwister<br>
